\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. R. vesicarius} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 336 (1753). Glaucous annual 5-30 cm. Leaves triangular, with long petioles. Each pedicel bearing paired flowers (primary and smaller secondary flower); valves of primary flowers 10-20 mm long, suborbicular, membranous, finely and densely reticulately veined, 2 valves of each flower with small tubercles, all with margins bent outwards so as to hide the tubercles and the secondary flower. Nut of primary flower 3·5-5 mm, greyish-brown; nut of secondary flower 2·8-4·5 mm, somewhat darker brown.{\i  Rocks and stony ground. S. Greece }({\i N.E. Peloponnisos}). Gr. ({\i N. Africa, S.W. Asia.})
\par

